goals.question: What is the distribution of x and y coordinates?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of x and y coordinates
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of the points in the 2D plane.

goals.question: What is the correlation between x and y coordinates?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of x and y coordinates with a regression line
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any relationship between the x and y coordinates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of distances from the reference point?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of the distances from the reference point.

goals.question: What is the average distance from the reference point?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the central tendency and spread of the distances from the reference point.

goals.question: What is the relationship between the distance from the reference point and the x and y coordinates?
goals.visualization: 3D scatter plot of x, y, and distance
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any relationship between the distance from the reference point and the x and y coordinates.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='x', y='y', hue='distance', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Distance', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='x', y='y')
    sns.regplot(data=data, x='x', y='y', scatter=False, color='red', label='Regression Line')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, bins=20)
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['distance'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of distances from the reference point?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='distance')
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average distance from the reference point?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
    
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['x'], data['y'], data['distance'], c=data['distance'], cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('X Coordinate')
    ax.set_ylabel('Y Coordinate')
    ax.set_zlabel('Distance')
    
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the distance from the reference point and the x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.colorbar(scatter, label='Distance')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
